00:15:55,840 --> 00:16:00,220
nation under God, indivisible, with liberty and justice for all.
在上帝之下的国家，不可分割，人人享有自由和正义。

314
00:16:00,220 --> 00:16:04,500
That part about one nation under God, that was added in the 50s as a kind of a way of
关于“在上帝之下的国家”那部分，是在50年代添加的，作为一种方式

315
00:16:04,500 --> 00:16:08,920
showing that America is not, quote unquote, a godless communist country.
来表明美国不是所谓的无神论共产主义国家。

316
00:16:08,920 --> 00:16:09,920
Wow.
哇。

317
00:16:09,920 --> 00:16:12,000
Yeah, because communism teaches, you know, no religion.
是的，因为共产主义教导，你知道，没有宗教。

318
00:16:12,000 --> 00:16:14,720
And so they, make sure we're not communist.
所以他们确保我们不是共产主义者。

319
00:16:14,720 --> 00:16:17,280
Okay, but we don't think that, right?
好的，但我们不这么认为，对吧？

320
00:16:17,280 --> 00:16:18,280
Yeah.
是的。

321
00:16:18,280 --> 00:16:19,920
I mean, I'm all about tolerance.
我的意思是，我完全支持宽容。

322
00:16:19,920 --> 00:16:21,520
So I think that's kind of absurd.
所以我认为这有点荒谬。

323
00:16:21,520 --> 00:16:26,120
Okay, so what I think is really interesting, though, is that every political speech, every
好的，但我认为非常有趣的是，每一次政治演讲，每一次

324
00:16:26,120 --> 00:16:31,960
time a political leader has to say something publicly, he'll always quote God, right?
政治领袖必须公开说些什么，他总会引用上帝，对吧？

325
00:16:31,960 --> 00:16:32,960
Right.
对。

326
00:16:32,960 --> 00:16:36,400
And they'll often end a speech with, you know, thank you and God bless America or something.
而且他们经常以“谢谢你们，上帝保佑美国”或类似的话结束演讲。

327
00:16:36,400 --> 00:16:37,400
Yeah, exactly.
是的，完全正确。

328
00:16:37,400 --> 00:16:40,520
Which, you know what, for me as a Canadian is really strange.
你知道吗，对我来说作为一个加拿大人，这真的很奇怪。

329
00:16:40,520 --> 00:16:47,240
Like if a Canadian president said, God bless Canada, everyone would, no one would know
就像如果加拿大总统说“上帝保佑加拿大”，每个人都会，没人知道

330
00:16:47,240 --> 00:16:48,240
what to do.
该做什么。

331
00:16:48,240 --> 00:16:49,240
Like, I don't know.
就像，我不知道。

332
00:16:49,240 --> 00:16:50,240
I don't know.
我不知道。

333
00:16:50,240 --> 00:16:53,360
Anyway, I had an ex-girlfriend who was British and she, like Tony Blair started with that
不管怎样，我有一个前女友是英国人，她，就像托尼·布莱尔开始那样

334
00:16:53,360 --> 00:16:54,360
a couple times.
几次。

335
00:16:54,360 --> 00:16:55,840
He said, you know, and God bless us all or something.
他说，你知道，上帝保佑我们所有人或类似的话。

336
00:16:55,840 --> 00:16:57,280
And she was just put off by it.
她对此感到反感。

337
00:16:57,280 --> 00:16:58,760
And she was like, the Brits will never take this.
她说，英国人永远不会接受这个。

338
00:16:58,760 --> 00:16:59,760
And they didn't.
他们确实没有。

339
00:16:59,760 --> 00:17:01,440
No one was impressed.
没有人被打动。

340
00:17:01,440 --> 00:17:02,440
All right.
好的。

341
00:17:02,440 --> 00:17:07,560
Well, an interesting feature of American history, politics and society.
嗯，这是美国历史、政治和社会的一个有趣特点。

342
